            <div class="lang-en">
                <h2>About the journal</h2>
                <p class="indent">The journal "Economic and Humanitarian Studies of Regions" is included in the <a href="docs/perechen_vak22.pdf" target="_blank">List of peer-reviewed scientific publications of the Higher Attestation Commission</a>, in which the main scientific results of dissertations for the degree of Candidate of Sciences, for the degree of Doctor of Sciences should be published and publishes materials of original theoretical and applied research on topical issues of pedagogy, philosophy and sociology of interest to the professorialteaching staff and researchers.</p>
                <p class="indent">The journal is published in accordance with Federal legislation on Mass Media, registered with the Federal Service for Supervision of Communications, Information Technology and Mass Communications (Roskomnadzor) – registration number PI No. FSS77-39740. The publication rules for authors were developed by the editorial board and approved by the editor-in-chief.</p>
                <p class="indent">The journal is published typographically in printed form, is published 1 time in 2 months, has an electronic full-text version, which is identical in content to the printed form and is posted on the Internet after the next issue is published at <a href="http://cegr.ru" target="_blank">www.cegr.ru</a></p>

                <h3 class="mt-2 mb-1">Thematic areas</h3>
                <p>5.4.4. Social structure, social institutions and processes (sociological sciences)</p>
                <p>5.7.1. Ontology and theory of cognition (philosophical sciences)</p>
                <p>5.7.7. Social and Political Philosophy (philosophical sciences)</p>
                <p>5.7.8. Philosophical anthropology, philosophy of culture (philosophical sciences)</p>
                <p>5.8.1. General pedagogy, history of pedagogy and education (pedagogical sciences)</p>
                <p class="mb20">5.8.7. Methodology and technology of vocational education (pedagogical sciences)</p>

